Vice President Kamala Harris spoke at Plumbers and Pipefitters Local 189 in Columbus, Ohio, thanking Secretary Marty Walsh and highlighting their work together on the Task Force on Worker Organizing and Empowerment. She praised Walsh's commitment to fighting for the working people of America and the dignity of work. Harris also acknowledged other leaders in attendance, including members of Ohio's Congressional Delegation. She emphasized the significance of the recently passed bipartisan Infrastructure Investment and Jobs Act, which will invest in roads, bridges, ports, airports, broadband, and clean water infrastructure. Harris emphasized the importance of union jobs and the administration's commitment to being the most pro-union in history. She discussed the need for the Build Back Better Act to further address the cost of living and strengthen registered apprenticeship programs. Harris expressed confidence that the Senate will pass the bill. She concluded by highlighting America's history of accomplishing big things in challenging times and encouraged belief in the future and what can be achieved when working together.